{"schema_version":"1.7.5","id":"GHSA-g839-vp47-wgh8","published":"2026-03-21T03:31:15Z","modified":"2026-03-24T19:17:20.862291Z","withdrawn":"2026-03-24T19:07:19Z","summary":"Duplicate Advisory: OpenClaw's Slack reaction/pin sender-policy consistency issue in non-message ingress","details":"## Duplicate Advisory\n\nThis advisory has been withdrawn because it is a duplicate of GHSA-rm2p-j3r7-4x4j]. This link is maintained to preserve external references.\n\n## Original Description\nOpenClaw versions prior to 2026.2.25 fail to consistently apply sender-policy checks to reaction_* and pin_* non-message events before adding them to system-event context. Attackers can bypass configured DM policies and channel user allowlists to inject unauthorized reaction and pin events from restricted senders.","affected":[{"package":{"name":"openclaw","ecosystem":"npm","purl":"pkg:npm/openclaw"},"ranges":[{"type":"SEMVER","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"last_affected":"2026.2.24"}]}],"database_specific":{"source":"https://github.com/github/advisory-database/blob/main/advisories/github-reviewed/2026/03/GHSA-g839-vp47-wgh8/GHSA-g839-vp47-wgh8.json"}}],"references":[{"type":"WEB","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/security/advisories/GHSA-rm2p-j3r7-4x4j"},{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-32899"},{"type":"WEB","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/commit/75dfb71e4e8b7c2feba5a8ca662f92ea840e0147"},{"type":"WEB","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/commit/aedf62ac7e669a89c7b299201bf6537dc6b12e0e"},{"type":"WEB","url":"https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/openclaw-sender-policy-bypass-in-slack-reaction-and-pin-event-handlers"}],"database_specific":{"cwe_ids":["CWE-863"],"github_reviewed":true,"github_reviewed_at":"2026-03-24T19:07:19Z","nvd_published_at":"2026-03-21T01:17:11Z","severity":"MODERATE"},"severity":[{"type":"CVSS_V3","score":"CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N"},{"type":"CVSS_V4","score":"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR